    <body>
      <div xml:id="NA289-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">itu piriviṭai paruvaṅ kaṇṭu colliyatu.</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">What is said after seeing the season in the time of separation.</p>
        </div>
      <div xml:id="NA289">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            amma vāḻi tōḻi kātalar</l>
<l>            nilampuṭai peyarva tāyiṉuṅ kūṟiya</l>
<l>            coṟpuṭai peyartalō vilarē vāṉa</l>
<l>            naḷikaṭaṉ mukantu ceṟitaka viruḷik</l>
<l>            kaṉaipeyal poḻintu kaṭuṅkural payiṟṟik </l>
<l>            kārcey teṉṉuḻai yatuvē yāyiṭaik</l>
<l>            kollaik kōvala relli māṭṭiya</l>
<l>            perumā vōṭiya pōla</l>
<l>            varuḷilē ṉamma vaḷiyeṉ yāṉē.</l>
            </lg>
        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>Alas, oh friend,</l>
<l rend="indent2">even if the ground turned upside down</l>
<l>[my] lover would not overturn the word he spoke.<note place="foot">The literal version is heavier: "as for overturning the word [my] lover spoke, not he".</note></l>
<l>The sky [is now] close to me<note place="foot">Here I take <term xml:lang="ta">vāṉam</term> as the subject of <term xml:lang="ta">ceytu</term> and <term xml:lang="ta">uḻaiyatu</term>, <term xml:lang="ta">kār</term> as subject of the other absolutives.</note>, making rain clouds,</l>
<l rend="indent2">drawing [water] from the vast sea, becoming densely dark,</l>
<l rend="indent2">pouring force the intense rain, repeating [thunder]</l>
<l rend="indent2">with fierce voice.</l>
<l rend="indent2">Just as the big animals running</l>
<l rend="indent3">when the cowherds have kindled light in the clearing,</l>
<l>I am without [his] consideration, alas, pitiable me.</l>
<lg type="alternate" sameAs="7+8b">
    <l>Felled just as the big roots</l>
    <l>that are kindled by the cowherds at night in the clearing<note place="foot">Actually, these two variants are indistinguishable in the manuscript version, and since both are slightly out of the normal, it is impossible to choose between them.</note></l>
</lg>
        </lg>
      </div>
